{
  "doc_id": "17355",
  "text": "SA is a potent inhibitor of the enzyme 5-ALA dehydratase. 5-ALA, a neurotoxic compound, accumulates and is excreted at high levels in patients with tyrosinemia type 1 and is believed to cause the acute neurological crises seen during decompensation [CITATION_1] . SA is also known to disrupt renal tubular function, heme synthesis and immune function [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
